Title: Traffik Trailer #1 (2018) | Movieclips Trailers
Comment:
This trailer is bad, but the movie itself looks interesting. I love Paula Patton. <3
Also this finally seems to be a movie about human trafficking, where the abducted woman not just escapes at the end, but really fights back (and where it goes not in a gory exploitation-direction like in Rape&Revenge-movies). I know that a film like "Eden" wasn't supposed to make you feel comfortable, but it would be more satisfying if the main character fought back like in this one.
"Refuse to become the victim" - I like this message.
Also it's important that a movie about this topic is made anyway, to raise awareness about this serious issue. I still think there are not enough.

Title: Traffik Trailer #1 (2018) | Movieclips Trailers
Comment: "Based on true events" is thrown around very liberally. I tried to research the story behind this movie, and it's not based on one. It's from only the directors mind. It's very misleading. I could make a movie about a murder in South America, never having been there or actually never even having read a story about any particular murder there, but because I know that murder occurs there I can say "based on true events" and get away with it by Hollywood standards. Once you realize that you have to start asking why the director choose this story with those characters, when he could have easily found a real trafficking story and made a movie that truly represents the issue.
